{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52f1000c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3103"},"text":"§ 3103.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Receivership","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f1000d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Appointment of a Receiver","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If the requirements of section 3101 are satisfied, a court may appoint a receiver for property in which the debtor has a substantial nonexempt interest if the United States shows reasonable cause to believe that there is a substantial danger that the property will be removed from the jurisdiction of the court, lost, concealed, materially injured or damaged, or mismanaged.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f1000e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Powers of Receiver","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f1000f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The appointing court may authorize a receiver—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f10010-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to take possession of real and personal property and sue for, collect, and sell obligations upon such conditions and for such purposes as the court shall direct; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f10011-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to administer, collect, improve, lease, repair or sell pursuant to section 3007 such real and personal property as the court shall direct.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"A receiver appointed to manage residential or commercial property shall have demonstrable expertise in the management of these types of property.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f10012-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Unless expressly authorized by order of the court, a receiver shall have no power to employ attorneys, accountants, appraisers, auctioneers, or other professional persons.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f10013-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Duration of Receivership","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A receivership shall not continue past the entry of judgment, or the conclusion of an appeal of such judgment, unless the court orders it continued under section 3203(e) or unless the court otherwise directs its continuation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f10014-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Accounts; Requirement to Report","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A receiver shall keep written accounts itemizing receipts and expenditures, describing the property and naming the depository of receivership funds. The receiver’s accounts shall be open to inspection by any person having an apparent interest in the property. The receiver shall file reports at regular intervals as directed by the court and shall serve the debtor and the United States with a copy thereof.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f10015-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Modification of Powers; Removal","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"On motion of the receiver or on its own initiative, the court which appointed the receiver may remove the receiver or modify the receiver’s powers at any time.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f10016-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Priority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If more than one court appoints a receiver for particular property, the receiver first qualifying under law shall be entitled to take possession, control, or custody of the property.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52f10017-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Compensation of Receivers","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f10018-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A receiver is entitled to such commissions, not exceeding 5 percent of the sums received and disbursed by him, as the court allows unless the court otherwise directs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f10019-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If, at the termination of a receivership, there are no funds in the hands of a receiver, the court may fix the compensation of the receiver in accordance with the services rendered and may direct the party who moved for the appointment of the receiver to pay such compensation in addition to the necessary expenditures incurred by the receiver which remain unpaid.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52f1001a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3103/g/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" At the termination of a receivership, the receiver shall file a final accounting of the receipts and disbursements and apply for compensation setting forth the amount sought and the services rendered by the receiver.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52f1001b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tXXXVI/s3611"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title XXXVI, § 3611","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4944"},"text":"104 Stat. 4944","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52f1001c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52f1001d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id52f1001e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective 180 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", and applicable with respect to certain actions for debts owed the United States pending in court on that effective date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/s3631"},"text":"section 3631 of Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
